<Author>Coopers4
<Content>Close to Christmas Market We stayed here for one night in late December on our way to Ireland. I reserved two rooms on the internet and had been impressed by the hotel's helpfulness and speed and ease in replying. The front desk staff were similarly pleasant and helpful when we arrived. Our rooms were small, as were the bathromms, but well heated and very clean. The breakfast was also good and all that we required. I chose the hotel because of its proximity to the centre of the city and the Christmas market, and indeed it was perfect for this. It was bitterly cold outside and it was great to be able to get back to the hotel in a couple of minutes. We were quite happy with our experience here and would definitely recommend it to others 
