<Author>ahmed_saffar
<Content>Three Stars, But The Location Covers Anything Else We have stayed here for four nights me and my wife. First impression was not that good because the room was small (then I knew that all of europe hotels are like that).Also, the reception area was small, and didn't seem to have room service or any outlets.But as soon as I talked to the receptionist I have realized how friendly she is and all of the hotel staff. They all speak very good english, though they don't mind helping you to learn some german (some german people does not accept it). Since our purpose in Frankfurt is tourism, we needed alot of help, where the hotel staff were very glad to offer.The hotel is very clean and the location is the best part of the hotel, it is in the middle of the city center. Everything is close by Shops, Bars, Restaurants, Coffee Shops, and even Banks. The shopping area is less than a minute walk, and the historical area (National Musseum, Cathedral, and Others) are just behind the hotel. The river Rhine and its surrounding walking path is 3 minutes walk.Bottom line its worth every penny we have paid. 
